description: This car was $29,995, but you can get it for $21,650 and save $8,345.  DON'T LET THIS OPPORTUNITY PASS YOU BY!!!!!!          Just Toys Classic Cars is very proud to present this 1973 Ford Maverick Shelby Tribute.  I know what you are saying, Shelby never did a maverick in the U.S.  You would be correct.  Carroll Shelby partnered up with a business man in Mexico by the name of Eduardo Velasques.  Velasques was a Shelby parts dealer in Mexico and the name was Shelby De Mexico.  You could buy parts for Mustangs, Galaxie's, and yes Maverick's.  This car is a tribute to Carroll and the type of things you could have gotten down there.  This car was built about 10 years ago and only has a few thousand miles on it since it was built.  This is just a really cool car that you are not going to see a 100 of at your local car show or cruise night.  The Gunmetal Gray Paint and Silver stripes are in great shape and as you see in the pics shines like there is no tomorrow.  This is a great culmination of Shelby's creations put in to this car.    So, now that we gave you a little bit of a history lesson, lets talk about the interior of this cool ride.  Once you open the driver door, you are going to see that the great fit and finish just carries forward.  The door panels are in great shape, and you do not see any rust in any of the jams anywhere.  Again, this is a very well put together car.  The cloth seats appear to be out of the fox body era of the Mustang and you will not see any rips or tears in them.  There has been a center console installed as well that fits like a glove around the Hurst shifter.  Safety is always a key, and you will see 4 point harnesses on the front as well as the back seats.  You can play all of your favorite tunes through the AM/FM/CD player that has been installed and they will sound awesome going down the road.  You should be itching by now to reach forward and give that ignition key a turn, so what do you say, shall we?    You give the gas a pump and hit that key and you listen to that 302 under the hood come to life and that instant, child like, ear to ear grin comes over your face as you give it a couple of revs.  That sweet sound is coming through a dual exhaust with Hedman headers and FlowMaster mufflers out back.  You will see an Edelbrock aluminum intake manifold and a 600 CFM Edelbrock carb sitting on top of this motor and Shelby valve covers to dress out the look.  All of this power is mated to a C4 automatic transmission and that all goes out to a Ford 8 rear end with 2.73 gears.  That means that you can have all the fun in the world with this car, and you will probably never see the top end of this motor.  The best of all worlds, fuel economy and fun all at the same time.    There has been attention paid to the underside of this car as well.  As you will see in the undercarriage pics, this is a very solid car underneath.  The brakes are manual, but they have been upgraded to Torino 11 disc in the front and the rear.  Every
